TITLE: Transforming onChange Args to State Value
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to transform the arguments passed to an `onChange` handler into the desired state value using the `onChangeArgsToValue` function. This is particularly useful when the `onChange` handler provides an event object instead of the direct state value, allowing for extraction and transformation of the relevant data from the event (e.g., extracting the input value from an event).
